article.headline: Indiana St. 68, Wichita St. 63
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Cole Holmstrom scored 16 points to lead Indiana State to a 68-63 victory over Wichita State on Wednesday. Marico Stinson had 13 points and Gabe Moore added 12 points for the Sycamores (11-4, 4-1 Missouri Valley Conference) in their sixth straight win. Holmstrom hit three 3-pointers as Indiana State shot 11-of-23 (48 percent) from behind the arc. A 3-pointer by Trent Wurtz with 9:03 left in the first half capped a 16-4 run for the Sycamores and gave Indiana State its largest lead of 12 points. The Sycamores led 33-30 at halftime and never trailed in the second half. P. J. Couisnard led Wichita State (10-6, 1-4) with 20 points and six rebounds. The Shockers had a 39-32 rebounding edge and outscored the Sycamores 44-14 in the paint, but never led by more than two points.
